				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Fatal Bard Kite in Dulak<a name="50788"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 8 04 5:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Not sure this is the right Forum but....I just dinged 53 last night and 6 aa's(come on Run3). Dulak's harbor is a blast for this level.  However, it can be quite busy on the 7th hammer at times since the new book arrived in Gulthak. I mainly pull the armory and the area infront of Windscorn(minus Initiate and Templar) as respect to other players. As I am waiting for some respawns inside the armory(I knew it was getting close) a small grp tried to invite my claimed area. I tried to tell them it was camped and could be dangerous in here(they were low 40's) when I pull my kite.  They attacked the Armory guards and basically ignored me.  I started my kite as I would normal(trying to avoid them)  as I'm getting all the mobs gathered,  one of the druids tried to pull one of my mobs with Ensnare.  Bad mistake...  I pulled aggro by running  by the mobs...no dmg.  The small grp quickly gained the aggro of the ENTIRE pull.  They were wiped out faster than the Lakers(sorry but true). As I regained my pull, I was seeing OOC  looking for rez's. Granted I thought if was kind of funny.  I wish other classes would realize how delicate our pulls as Bards can be.  I was honestly waiting for a GM to contact me asking if I trained them or not. I didn't(honestly, but did think about it). They did complain to their guild officer who did contact me.  Funny part is, he repromanded them for trying to mess with a Bards kite. He's also my RL friend who is also playing a Bard. I guess someone must play a Bard to truely understand us.  /rant off</span></td>
