			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I had a similar experience in ME the other day.  I was attempting to help a guildmate farm the ME shard for the VT key.
<br />

<br />
I told him ahead of time not to heal me at all if I get low on health, to just let me die and rez later.
<br />

<br />
Well, he listened to that part, but tried to help by rooting some of my 25-mob swarm (I was swarm kiting, not AE).  That was pretty bad news, because he pulled off about 5 mobs onto him.  He was able to root some more, but eventually died.  Meanwhile, I was fine.   I eventually killed them all except some shaman-like mob which kept CH'ing himself.
<br />

<br />
So if you're ever grouping with a caster while swarming kiting (AE is not quite so touchy after the first few AE's), make sure to tell them not to cast *anything* except self-buffs or heals unless specifically asked to.
<br />
</span></td>
