				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fatal Bard Kite in Dulak<a name="50903"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 9 04 10:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Man this is the second thread about bad experiences in Gunthak and Dulak, makes me glad I never really liked either zone enough to hang out there for too long. My advice? Find another place to hunt guys, it's not tucking your tail and running so don't choke on your pride, stay away from people, the bottom line is that you can tell everyone you see for the next year all about bard kiting and they still won't give you the space you need unlesss they try it themselves. Who needs the hassle? I know I don't. I avoid crowded areas for a good reason, besides the fact that occasional people are inconsiderate, a lot of people just don't know or just don't get it. Dulak and Gunthak can both get very crowded and I know it's not your fault someone waltzed in and started messing with you, but you have to expect these things in areas like the previously mentioned, where crowds and inexperience can create some hairy situations. Be better than that, and avoid the headaches all together for yourself. I don't go to PC, it's a huge pain in the a$, instead I go to Unrest, same modifier, no crowds. I only AEd in Dulak once and as soon as I saw a group not far from me, I took off, maybe I just need more space than most folks but I hate soloing around other people, makes me nervous because people are so unpredicatble. Have you checked out Eastern Wastes? You can swarm the h*ll out of Ulthorks and Orcs all the way through your 40s, you can AE the crap out of them too, plenty of spawns to pick from and not a person for MILES, you'll be lucky to run into one. Ice clad is the same way and they're right next to each other, you can even AE the wolves in Great Divide. We are a social class for sure, but when we solo we need more room than most, don't even let the situation present itself for others to interfere, stay away from them all together. 
<br />
Just my 2cp
<br />
 <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
