				<td colspan="2"><span>Gunthak &amp; Dulak were almost always completely empty until recently when they added the stone there.  6 people in an entire zone is practically empty for most zones (crushbone is the one exception that comes to mind perhaps).  
<br />

<br />
Having done Eastern Wastes when I was leveling my bard and having done it in Dulak on my alts, I'd rather do Dulak since the exp is better due to zone bonuses and/or level of mobs and the cash/trash loot is much better.  
<br />

<br />
Dulak could handle 6 xp groups easily (probably closer to 10-12).  For 1 group to HAVE to pull right next to the where the bard was already set up is just that group trying to cause issues or plain being stupid.  
<br />

<br />
Yes bards (and other kiters) need to be considerate of groups in the area by keeping their kite under control (doesn't count stupid people screwing with your kite) and not monopolizing the entire zone.  However, bards do not need to pack up and leave just because another person is in the zone with them.
<br />
